I love how the 80's pop fashions and architecture were trying to look so futuristic. And now being in the future, these hip "new" fashions merely resemble a not quite exciting version of the past.

But oddly enough the new school kids of today are trying to look like they're from the 80's.

So were the 80's truly a hint into our present future? Or are we currently in the state of art imitating life, imitating art...
